[h3]Escalation Tiers[/h3]
[list]
[*]Pop-raiding escalation is simpler: four tiers instead of six, with nicer round caps. Tier 0 captures up to 10% of the target's population, tier 1 up to 25%, tier 2 up to 50%, and tier 3 takes everything.
[*]The escalation popup's "press" button now shows exactly how many pops the next tier will take, including the final "take everything" option.
[*]Existing saves have their in-progress raid counters reset to tier 0 so the new caps apply cleanly.
[/list]

[h3]Opportunistic Raiding[/h3]
[list]
[*]A raiding war goal now only grants raiding against its actual target — the enemy you declared the war on. Their allies and co-defenders count as secondary targets and need opportunistic authorization, same as anyone in a non-raiding war.
[*]You'll be asked for authorization the first time you actually try to raid a secondary target: raiding-stance bombardment, winning a ground invasion, or monthly auto-raid kicking in on a planet you occupy.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*]Renamed an economic-categories file for better compatibility with other mods — Harvesting Protocol's unity and energy bonuses no longer silently do nothing in some load orders.
[/list]
